.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_AAF.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"get_AAF — get_AAF","text":"model model want compute AAF nvar can choose integer parameter prefer add explanatory variables order appear model. use name_var parameter. name_var list explanatory variables want compute AAF vars_dep string name variable want explain data data used fit model (variable name_var vars_dep) nbootstrap integer n bootsrap replication want. default, 50. nperm Number permutation modalities variable compute AAF","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_AAF.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"get_AAF — get_AAF","text":"sf table result AAF computation","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_AAF.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"get_AAF — get_AAF","text":"","code":"set.seed(9876) data <- data.frame(    \"var_dep\" = as.factor(sample(c(rep_len(c(0, 1), length.out = 1000)), size = 100)),    \"var_1\" = as.factor(sample(c(rep_len(c(1, 2, 3), length.out = 1000)), size = 100)),    \"var_2\" = as.factor(sample(c(rep_len(c(3, 1, 2), length.out = 100)), size = 100))    ) glmmodel <- glm(var_dep ~ var_1 + var_2,                 data = data, family = binomial(\"logit\")) res <- get_AAF(model = glmmodel, nvar = 3, vars_dep = \"var_dep\", data = data,                nbootstrap = 5) #> [1] \"Using random variable\" #> [1] \"COMPUTE\" #res <- get_AAF(model = glmmodel, #               name_var = c(\"var_1\", \"var_2\"), #              vars_dep = \"var_dep\", data = data, nbootstrap = 5)"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_list.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"get_list — get_list","title":"get_list — get_list","text":"Get list names variables pass parameter","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_list.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"get_list — get_list","text":"","code":"get_list(name_var = NULL)"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_list.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"get_list — get_list","text":"name_var list variable want pass name list","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_list.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"get_list — get_list","text":"list zero named variable name_var parameter","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_list.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"get_list — get_list","text":"","code":"vec <- get_list(name_var = c(\"var1\", \"var2\"))"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_yuleq.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Get Yule's Q — get_yuleq","title":"Get Yule's Q — get_yuleq","text":"Get Yule's Q","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_yuleq.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Get Yule's Q — get_yuleq","text":"","code":"get_yuleq(   vars_dep = NULL,   name_var = c(),   data = NULL,   source = \"\",   alpha = 0.01,   weight = NULL )"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_yuleq.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Get Yule's Q — get_yuleq","text":"vars_dep string name dependant variable use one variable 2x2 table name_var vector explanatory variable want compute Yule's Q data dataframe variable named source string name data source alpha integer alpha value fisher.test IC weight vector weigths corresponding dataframe individuals weights","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_yuleq.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Get Yule's Q — get_yuleq","text":"gt table Yule's computed variable name_var","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/get_yuleq.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Get Yule's Q — get_yuleq","text":"","code":"data <- graphPAF::Hordaland_data get_yuleq(vars_dep = \"y\", name_var = c(\"y\",  \"urban.rural\"),                     data = data, source = \"dataSource - Year\",                     alpha = 0.01)     Q de Yule     Sur la variable y                   Q de Yule       se.Q       ll       ul       p.value     urban.rural 0 - Ref -    1 24.32% 0.019 19.33% 29.18% 0.000 Source : dataSource - Year"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/result_tab.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"result_tab — result_tab","title":"result_tab — result_tab","text":"Get result table , AME AAF","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/result_tab.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"result_tab — result_tab","text":"","code":"result_tab(   model = NULL,   var_ref = NULL,   var_names = NULL,   res_AAF = NULL,   source = \"\",   data = data.frame() )"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/result_tab.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"result_tab — result_tab","text":"model model used perform statistical analysis var_ref variable explain statistical model var_names list name variable want show contingency tables res_AAF result AAF computation get_AAF() function (done outside function length computation) source Data source information add plots data data used statistical analysis","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/result_tab.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"result_tab — result_tab","text":"gt table","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/reference/result_tab.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"result_tab — result_tab","text":"","code":"set.seed(9876) data <- data.frame(    \"var_dep\" = as.factor(sample(c(rep_len(c(0, 1), length.out = 1000)), size = 100)),    \"var_1\" = as.factor(sample(c(rep_len(c(1, 2, 3), length.out = 1000)), size = 100)),    \"var_2\" = as.factor(sample(c(rep_len(c(3, 1, 2), length.out = 100)), size = 100))    ) glmmodel <- glm(var_dep ~ var_1 + var_2, data = data, family = binomial(\"logit\")) res <- get_AAF(model = glmmodel, nvar = 3, vars_dep = \"var_dep\", data = data,                nbootstrap = 5) #> [1] \"Using random variable\" #> [1] \"COMPUTE\"  if (FALSE) res_tab <- result_tab(model = glmmodel, var_ref = \"var_dep\",                       var_names = c(\"var_1\", \"var_2\"),                       res_AAF = resAAF$res, source = \"TESTDATA\", data = data) # \\dontrun{}"},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/news/index.html","id":"socialfacts-120","dir":"Changelog","previous_headings":"","what":"SocialFacts 1.2.0","title":"SocialFacts 1.2.0","text":"First CRAN submission rewrite entire example passes test exept one crashing example result_tab","code":""},{"path":"https://geminy3.github.io/SocialFacts/news/index.html","id":"socialfacts-100","dir":"Changelog","previous_headings":"","what":"SocialFacts 1.0.0","title":"SocialFacts 1.0.0","text":"Initial CRAN submission.","code":""}]
